Announcing the #HiggsBoson discovery
#CERN70 – Part 20

This #ThrowbackThursday we take a look at a milestone in the history of science.

At 9.00 on 4 July 2012, Joe Incandela and Fabiola Gianotti, the spokespersons for the @CMSexperiment and @ATLASexperiment, took the floor in front of an excited audience to present the latest data from their experiments: the discovery of the Higgs boson.

This date marked the start of a new adventure for #ParticlePhysics. Since the discovery, the two experiments have carried out a lot of work to define the new particle.

Here we see:
1️⃣ Belgian theorist, François Englert (left), and British theorist, Peter Higgs (right), in CERN's Main Auditorium, speaking after the announcement of the discovery. They were awarded the @NobelPrize in Physics the following year;

2️⃣ Candidate Higgs boson events from collisions between protons in the #LHC, in the CMS experiment;

3️⃣ Candidate Higgs boson events from collisions between protons in the LHC, in the ATLAS experiment;

4️⃣ Fabiola Gianotti, spokesperson for the ATLAS collaboration and current CERN Director-General, presenting the ATLAS results on the search for the Higgs boson;

5️⃣ CERN Director-General Rolf Heuer (left), and ATLAS and CMS experiment spokespersons Fabiola Gianotti (centre) and Joe Incandela (right), following the announcement of the results on the search for the Higgs boson;

